# =============================================================================
# .dockerignore — shrinks the Docker build context (repo ROOT) for the
# production images built by iac/production/{backend,frontend}.Dockerfile.
#
# Both Dockerfiles use the repo root as the build context and COPY only:
#   - pnpm-lock.yaml, pnpm-workspace.yaml, package.json   (root manifests)
#   - apps/backend  /  apps/frontend                      (app source + config)
#   - iac/production/nginx.conf                            (frontend runtime)
#
# node_modules and build output are always produced INSIDE the build stages,
# so anything the images don't strictly need is excluded here. Re-includes (!)
# below bring back the few files a broad ignore would otherwise drop.
# =============================================================================

# --- Dependencies & package-manager caches ----------------------------------
**/node_modules
.pnpm-store
**/.pnpm-store

# --- Build outputs, compiler & tooling caches -------------------------------
**/dist
**/.angular
**/.turbo
**/coverage
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# --- Version control & CI metadata ------------------------------------------
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.github

# --- Editor / tooling / dev-environment -------------------------------------
.vscode
.idea
.devcontainer
.claude
.tool-versions
.editorconfig
.releaserc.json
skills-lock.json

# --- Environment files & secrets (never bake into an image layer) -----------
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# --- Documentation & non-build markdown -------------------------------------
docs
**/*.md

# --- OS cruft & logs --------------------------------------------------------
**/.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
**/*.log
npm-debug.log*
pnpm-debug.log*

# --- Infrastructure: drop all of iac/ EXCEPT the nginx config the frontend
#     runtime stage copies. (Parent dirs are re-included step-by-step so the
#     nested exception survives on every builder version.) -------------------
iac/*
!iac/production
iac/production/*
!iac/production/nginx.conf
